
Overview of noun fury

The noun fury has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (4) fury, rage, madness -- (a feeling of intense anger; "hell hath no fury like a woman scorned"; "his face turned red with rage")
2. (3) craze, delirium, frenzy, fury, hysteria -- (state of violent mental agitation)
3. (3) ferocity, fierceness, furiousness, fury, vehemence, violence, wildness -- (the property of being wild or turbulent; "the storm's violence")
4. Fury, Eumenides, Erinyes -- ((classical mythology) the hideous snake-haired monsters (usually three in number) who pursued unpunished criminals)
